    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-25T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-25T08:00:00-05:00" n="154"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">399.10–<gloss target="#t_UPU1">UPU</gloss>/1–2551:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-25T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >January 25, 1951—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>779. Embassy approached <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> as requested
                        <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 707 January 24. Egyptian position
                    will be that as hosts they will abstain unless their vote constitutes deciding
                    vote which case will request adjournment to study situation.</p>
                <p>British Embassy has just informed Embassy (after telephoning London seeking
                    modified instructions) that they have received positive instructions from London
                    to vote against US resolution against compromise and for Russian resolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
